Subject: FEATURE: new transform to optimize uniform expressions
Date: Wed, 26 Jan 2011 15:34:57 -0700
Cc: Kevin Jones <kjones5863@gmail.com>
X-Mailer: Apple Mail (2.936)

This transform should detect expression trees of the form:

uniform(l,u) OP uniform(l',u')

and rearrange the tree as appropriate.

If OP is + , then this would mean to create a new expression:
	uniform(l+l',u+u')

If OP is - then this would mean to create a new expression:
	uniform(l-u',u-l')

If OP is min then this would mean to create a new expression:
  	uniform(min(l,l'),min(u,u'))

If OP is max then this would mean to create a new expression:
  	uniform(max(l,l'),max(u,u'))

Other useful transforms:

uniform(l,u) * n

where n is a non-negative constant, results in

uniform(n*l,n*u)

floor(uniform(l,u)) <=> uniform(floor(l),floor(u))

ceil(uniform(l,u)) <=> uniform(ceil(l),ceil(u))

uniform(uniform(l,u),uniform(l',u')) <=> uniform(l,u')

Did I missing any?

Chris

